{"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"cancel()","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:22ComposableArchitecture13TestStoreTaskV6cancelyyYaF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"cancel","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() ","kind":"text"},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/teststoretask\/cancel()"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"cancel"},{"text":"() ","kind":"text"},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can be handy when a feature needs to start a long-living effect when the feature appears,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"but cancellation of that effect is handled by the parent when the feature disappears. Such a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"feature is difficult to exhaustively test in isolation because there is no action in its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain that cancels the effect:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let store = TestStore(\/* ... *\/)","","let onAppearTask = await store.send(.onAppear)","\/\/ Assert what is happening in the feature","","await onAppearTask.cancel() \/\/ ✅ Cancel the task to simulate the feature disappearing."],"syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cancels the underlying task and waits for it to finish."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/Composabl